Damaturu- The Yobe state Governor and Chairman of the All Progressives Congress Caretaker/Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee, Mai Mala Buni, has assured greater roles with more opportunities to women in the party. The Chairman gave the assurance in commemoration of the International Women’s Day celebration. Buni said the party will support women to aspire for more elective offices. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! “More women will be given more roles and opportunities to flay the party’s flag in future elections. “I urge women politicians to take advantage of the ongoing membership registration and revalidation exercise to register to aspire for public offices on the platform of the party” Governor Buni said. Do Not Abandon Projects Started By Your Predecessors, Okowa Warns Newly Elected LG Chairmen Fayose Hails Nigerian Women On International Women’s Day The Chairman Caretaker committee said APC remains the most women friendly party in Nigeria in which women can easily realise their political ambitions. “The APC administration would continue to support Nigeria women to actualize their political and professional ambitions locally and internationally” the chairman said.